{"title_page": "WAFZ-FM", "text_new": "{{Infobox radio station\n| name                 = WAFZ-FM\n| image                = Logo-la-ley3.png\n| city                 = [[Immokalee, Florida]]\n| area                 = \n| branding             = ''La Ley 92.1 FM''\n| slogan               = \"LA Que Manda\" \n| airdate              = 1987-06-30 (as WIKX-FM)\n| frequency            = 92.1 [[MHz]]\n| repeater              = WAFZ AM 1490, Immokalee\n| format               = [[Regional Mexican]]\n| power                = \n| erp                  = 5,600 [[watt]]s\n| haat                 = 100 meters\n| class                = A\n| facility_id          = 47387\n| coordinates          = {{coord|26|26|54.00|N| 81|16|17.00|W|region:US_type:city}}\n| callsign_meaning     =\n| former_callsigns     = WIKX-FM (1987-1988)<br>WCOO (1988-1994)<br>WGCQ (1994-2002)\n| affiliations         = \n| owner                = Glades Media Company LLC\n| licensee             = \n| sister_stations      =\n| webcast              = [http://radio.securenetsystems.net/v5/wafz Listen Live]\n| website              = [http://www.wafz.com wafz.com]\n}}\n\n'''WAFZ-FM''' (92.1 [[FM broadcasting|FM]]) is a [[radio station]] licensed to [[Immokalee, Florida]], broadcasting a [[Regional Mexican]] format. The format plays a variety of new and current hits on the Regional Mexican format. At one time Also played [[Tejano music]] Music in the 1980s on its sister station WAFZ-AM. In its beginnings WAFZ had been WZOR-AM 1490 and English programming adult contemporary music and news on for the morning until 3pm. Then it changed its format to regional Mexican/tejano. The early DJs that worked there were Gabino Soliz, \"EL CHAVO ALEGRE\" and Irma Ayala. The station continued on the air for a long time until the mid 1990s then it went silent for a while until what is now WAFZ was bought by Glades Media and transmitted simultaneous what WAFZ FM was playing (a regional Mexican format). The Current Format of  WAFZ is a young Regional Mexican, playing newer top40 hits of the Regional Mexican Genre. At one time before this it was a country station, then it was an oldies, Christian, Spanish contemporary pop. It is  Licensed to [[Immokalee, Florida]], United States, the station is currently owned by Glades Media Company LLC.\n\nWAFZ's programming is also heard on '''WAFZ''' AM 1490 in Immokalee.\n\n==External links==\n*{{FM station data|WAFZ}}\n{{AM station data|WAFZ}}\n\n{{Fort Myers Radio}}\n{{Spanish Radio Stations in Florida}}\n\n[[Category:Radio stations in Florida|AFZ]]\n[[Category:Radio stations established in 1987]]\n[[Category:1987 establishments in Florida]]\n\n\n{{Florida-radio-station-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox radio station\n| name                 = WAFZ-FM\n| image                = Logo-la-ley3.png\n| city                 = [[Immokalee, Florida]]\n| area                 = \n| branding             = ''La Ley 92.1 FM''\n| slogan               = \"LA Que Manda\" \n| airdate              = 1987-06-30 (as WIKX-FM)\n| frequency            = 92.1 [[MHz]]\n| repeater              = WAFZ AM 1490, Immokalee\n| format               = [[Regional Mexican]]\n| power                = \n| erp                  = 5,600 [[watt]]s\n| haat                 = 100 meters\n| class                = A\n| facility_id          = 47387\n| coordinates          = {{coord|26|26|54.00|N| 81|16|17.00|W|region:US_type:city}}\n| callsign_meaning     =\n| former_callsigns     = WIKX-FM (1987-1988)<br>WCOO (1988-1994)<br>WGCQ (1994-2002)\n| affiliations         = \n| owner                = Glades Media Company LLC\n| licensee             = \n| sister_stations      =\n| webcast              = [http://radio.securenetsystems.net/v5/wafz Listen Live]\n| website              = [http://www.wafz.com wafz.com]\n}}\n\n'''WAFZ-FM''' (92.1 [[FM broadcasting|FM]]) is a [[radio station]] licensed to [[Immokalee, Florida]], broadcasting a [[Regional Mexican]] format. The format plays a variety of new and current hits on the Regional Mexican format. At one time Also played [[Tejano music]] Music in the 1980s on its sister station WAFZ-AM. In its beginnings WAFZ had been WZOR-AM 1490 and English programming adult contemporary music and news on for the morning until 3pm. Then it changed its format to regional Mexican/tejano. The early DJ's that worked there were Gabino Soliz, \"EL CHAVO ALEGRE\" and Irma Ayala. The station continued on the air for a long time until the mid 1990s then it went silent for a while until what is now WAFZ was bought by Glades Media and transmitted simultaneous what WAFZ FM was playing (a regional Mexican format). The Current Format of  WAFZ is a young Regional Mexican, playing newer top40 hits of the Regional Mexican Genre. At one time before this it was a country station, then it was an oldies, Christian, Spanish contemporary pop. It is  Licensed to [[Immokalee, Florida]], United States, the station is currently owned by Glades Media Company LLC.\n\nWAFZ's programming is also heard on '''WAFZ''' AM 1490 in Immokalee.\n\n==External links==\n*{{FM station data|WAFZ}}\n{{AM station data|WAFZ}}\n\n{{Fort Myers Radio}}\n{{Spanish Radio Stations in Florida}}\n\n[[Category:Radio stations in Florida|AFZ]]\n[[Category:Radio stations established in 1987]]\n[[Category:1987 establishments in Florida]]\n\n\n{{Florida-radio-station-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Alistair1978", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo (viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WAFZ-FM"}
