od Hunter]]'' || Poe || Posthumous release, (final film role)\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1962 || ''[[The Lloyd Bridges Show]]'' || Takahashi || Episode: \"Yankee Stay Here\"\n|-\n| 1962\u20131963 || ''[[Ensign O'Toole]]'' || Various roles || 3 episodes\n|-\n| 1962\u20131965 || ''[[McHale's Navy]]'' || Various roles || 9 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1963 || ''[[The Gallant Men]]'' || Frank Fakuda || Episode: \"One Puka Puka\"\n|-\n| ''[[77 Sunset Strip]]'' || Iko Nakayama || Episode: \"Stranger from the Sea\"\n|-\n| 1964 || ''[[Arrest and Trial]]'' || Kyoto || Episode: \"Signals of an Ancient Flame\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1964\u20131965 || ''[[Broadside (TV series)|Broadside]]'' || Japanese Commander / Captain Osato || 2 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Burke's Law (1963 TV series)|Burke's Law]]'' || Pete / Happy Tuava || 2 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1965 || ''[[I Dream of Jeannie]]'' || Kato || Episode:  \"Jeannie and the Marriage Caper\"\n|-\n| ''[[Gidget (TV series)|Gidget]]'' || Casey || Episode: \"The War Between Men, Women and Gidget\"\n|-\n| ''[[The Wackiest Ship in the Army (TV series)|The Wackiest Ship in the Army]]'' ||  T. Vushikori / Captain Kulijame || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 1965\u20131966 || ''[[I Spy (1965 TV series)|I Spy]]'' || Jimmy / Baby Face || 3 episodes\n|-\n| 1966 || ''[[The Green Hornet (TV series)|The Green Hornet]]'' || Low Sing || Episode: \"The Praying Mantis\"\n|-\n| 1966, 1968 || ''[[The F.B.I. (TV series)|The F.B.I.]]'' || Angry Youth / Yoshimura || 2 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1967 || ''[[The Time Tunnel]]'' || Lt. Nakamura || Episode: \"Kill Two by Two\"\n|-\n| ''[[F Troop]]'' || Samurai Warrior || Episode: \"From Karate with Love\"\n|-\n| ''[[Vacation Playhouse]]'' || Simba || Episode: \"Alfred of the Amazon\"\n|-\n| 1968 || ''[[The Big Valley]]'' || Wong Lo || Episode: \"Rimfire\"\n|-\n| 1970 || ''[[The Challenge (1970 film)|The Challenge]]'' || Yuro || Television film\n|-\n| 19