{"title_page": "Q (song)", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{refimprove|date=June 2015}}\n{{Notability|Music|date = January 2016}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Q\n| cover      = fsol - mental cube - Q.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = Mental Cube\n| album      = [[Earthbeat (The Future Sound of London album)|Earthbeat]]\n| released   = 1990, 1991\n| format     = [[12-inch single]]\n| recorded   = Earthbeat Studios\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Techno]]\n| length     = 8:20 <br> 13:28\n| label      = Buzz ''BZZXL 106033'' <br> Flarenasch ''180 996''\n| writer     = [[Brian Dougans]]<br/>[[Garry Cobain]]\n| producer   = FSOL\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[The Future Sound of London]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[I Can See For Miles (Yunie song)|I Can See for Miles]]\n | prev_year  = 1990\n | title      = Q\n | year       = 1990\n | next_title = [[So This Is Love (single)|So This Is Love]]\n | next_year  = 1991\n}}\n}}\n\n'''\"Q\"''' is a single released in 1990/1991 by ''Mental Cube'' (better known as [[Future Sound of London]]). It is a widely respected dance classic among [[DJ]]s and has a distinctive bleeping, electronica feel reminiscent of work by [[Orbital (band)|Orbital]].<ref>[http://www.secondthought.co.uk/fsol/ The Future Sound of London - Welcome to the Galaxial Pharmaceutical v7] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/66MEOj6U7?url=http://www.secondthought.co.uk/fsol/ |date=2012-03-22 }}</ref>\n\n==Track listings==\n\n===1990 release===\n# Q (Original) (4:10)\n# Q (Santa Monica Mix) (4:10)\n\n===1991 release===\n# Q (Remix) (4:51)\n# Q (Santa Monica Mix) (4:12)\n# Q (Original Mix) (4:15)\n\n==Crew==\n*Artwork By One Way\n*Artwork By [Sleeve Computer Graphic] Fr\u00e9d\u00e9rick Avrado\n*Producer - FSOL, Yage\n*Written By - B. Dougans, G. Cobain\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{discogs release|id=128804|name=''Q''}}\n\n{{The Future Sound of London}}\n\n[[Category:1990 songs]]\n[[Category:1991 singles]]\n[[Category:The Future Sound of London songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{refimprove|date=June 2015}}\n{{Notability|Music|date = January 2016}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Q\n| cover      = fsol - mental cube - Q.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = Mental Cube\n| album      = [[Earthbeat (The Future Sound of London album)|Earthbeat]]\n| released   = 1990, 1991\n| format     = [[12-inch single]]\n| recorded   = Earthbeat Studios\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Techno]]\n| length     = 8:20 <br> 13:28\n| label      = Buzz ''BZZXL 106033'' <br> Flarenasch ''180 996''\n| writer     = [[Brian Dougans]]<br/>[[Garry Cobain]]\n| producer   = FSOL\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[The Future Sound of London]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[I Can See For Miles (Yunie song)|I Can See for Miles]]\n | prev_year  = 1990\n | title      = Q\n | year       = 1990\n | next_title = [[So This Is Love (single)|So This Is Love]]\n | next_year  = 1991\n}}\n}}\n\n'''\"Q\"''' is a single released in 1990/1991 by ''Mental Cube'' (better known as [[Future Sound of London]]). It is a widely respected dance classic among [[DJ]]'s and has a distinctive bleeping, electronica feel reminiscent of work by [[Orbital (band)|Orbital]].<ref>[http://www.secondthought.co.uk/fsol/ The Future Sound of London - Welcome to the Galaxial Pharmaceutical v7] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/66MEOj6U7?url=http://www.secondthought.co.uk/fsol/ |date=2012-03-22 }}</ref>\n\n==Track listings==\n\n===1990 release===\n# Q (Original) (4:10)\n# Q (Santa Monica Mix) (4:10)\n\n===1991 release===\n# Q (Remix) (4:51)\n# Q (Santa Monica Mix) (4:12)\n# Q (Original Mix) (4:15)\n\n==Crew==\n*Artwork By One Way\n*Artwork By [Sleeve 