{"title_page": "Dimples D.", "text_new": "'''Crystal Smith''', better known by her [[stage name]] '''Dimples D.''', is an [[United States|American]] [[rapping|rapper]] who became a [[one-hit wonder]] in 1990.\n\n==Sucker DJ==\nDimples D. was selected as the [[Singing|vocalist]] for a track by [[hip hop]] [[record producer|producer]] [[Marley Marl]] entitled \"Sucker DJs (I Will Survive)\", released on [[Party Time Records]] in 1983. \"Sucker DJs\" was written by Crystal Smith / Williams / Kaye / Montenegro.\n\nThe song\u2014an [[answer song]] to [[Run\u2013D.M.C.]]'s \"[[Sucker M.C.'s|Sucker M.C.s (Krush-Groove 1)]]\"\u2014did not sell in quantity upon its first release, but [[Ben Liebrand]] reworked the [[song]] in 1990, including a [[sampling (music)|sample]] of the [[theme music|theme song]] from the American [[situation comedy|sitcom]], ''[[I Dream of Jeannie]]''. Upon re-release, the song went to [[Record chart#Chart hit|#1]] in [[Australia]], #17 in the [[UK Singles Chart]],<ref name=\"British Hit Singles & Albums\">{{cite book\n| first= David\n| last= Roberts\n| year= 2006\n| title= British Hit Singles & Albums\n| edition= 19th\n| publisher= Guinness World Records Limited\n| location= London\n| isbn= 1-904994-10-5\n| page= 131}}</ref> and [[Record chart|charted]] in many countries in [[Europe]].\n\n==Singles in charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:24em;\"| Single\n! colspan=\"7\"| Peak positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! width=\"35\"| <small>[[ARIA Charts|AUS]]\n! width=\"35\"| <small>[[\u00d63 Austria Top 40|AUT]]\n! width=\"35\"| <small>[[Ultratop|BEL<br>(Fla)]]\n! width=\"35\"| <small>[[Media Control Charts|GER]]</small><br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.de/suche.asp?search=dimples+d&x=0&y=0&country=de |title=Dimples D. - German Chart |publisher=charts.de |accessdate=2014-04-22}}</ref>\n! width=\"35\"| <small>[